<TITLE> Tk 1.5 crore cash award for cricketers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 21 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Cricket Board on Tuesday announced a Tk 1.5 crore cash award for the national cricket team after their first-ever away Test series win over West Indies. BCB president Lt Gen Sina Ibn Jamali declared it in a hurriedly arranged media briefing to express his satisfaction over the national team performance in the West Indies. The national team are supposed to get Tk 1.3 crore cash award for their series win and the board announced additional Tk 20 lakh for them as an incentive. Hailing the first-ever away series win, the BCB president said, "With this win the Bangladesh cricket team has fulfilled the dreams and aspirations of millions. "I congratulate the players and team management, the cricket operations department and everyone associated with the team. Our continuing effort to develop cricket in Bangladesh will gather more momentum through this victory." The BCB president also thanked the national team sponsor Grameenphone. "Grameenphone is our long-term partner and are integral part of this success. I also take this opportunity to felicitate our sponsor partners and all those who have congratulated us on this historic achievement
